- What is Docker?
  => Docker is an open platform for developing, shipping, and running applications.
  => Docler is platform which packages an application and all its dependencies together in the form of containers
  =>Docker is not a virchual machine this is a container becouse VM have a V-Ram etc but Docker has not.

- Docker File
  => Text Documents which contains all the commands that a user can all on the command line to assemble an image.

- Docker Image
  => Template to create docker container

- Docker Container
  => Running instance of the docker image. 
     Container hold entire packeges to run application.

[ Dockerfile  ===_build_===>  Docker Image ===_Run_===> Docker Container ]
